    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-11T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-11T12:00:00-05:00" n="757"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d757">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/1453</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SWG1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-11T18:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 11, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 11.54 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3228 [<hi rend="italic">3328</hi>]. Joint telegram from Allied ministers at Jassy
                    dated March 9:</p>
                <p>We made [the President of] the Council the presumptive declaration announced in
                    [our] telegram of yesterday regarding war material.<note n="1" xml:id="d757fn1"
                        >Apparently referring to telegram of the same date, <hi rend="italic"
                            >infra.</hi>
                    </note> General <persName corresp="#p_AA1">Averesco</persName> assured us in the
                    clearest terms that no demand for the delivery of Russian or Roumanian material
                    had ever been formulated by the Germans. He added that if such a demand were
                    made it would be rejected considering that when accepting to negotiate with the
                    enemy he had had especially in view the preservation of the Army so as to
                    reserve the future and that the Army without material in the geographical
                    situation of Roumania would be non-existing. We have taken note of these
                    assurances which, however, we transmit with the reservations that the present
                    situation … impose.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SWG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sharp</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
